 Dante’s Cult of Truth presents an intertextual literary history, one which seeks to maintain the uncanniness of literature, while imagining history to be neither linear nor clearly distinguishable from literature itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aPoetics. 0aPoetryxHistory and criticism. 7aPOETRY / European / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999z97831107136020 cprintz978082231117140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822399568?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822399568423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822399568/original  a978-3-11-071360-2  Duke University Press Archive eBook-Package 1964-1999c1964d1999  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles